This paper deals with the design of an efficient data delivery solution in opportunistic networks, which is a subfield of computer networking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to quantify the friendship strength among pairs of nodes in the network, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper considers the selfishness of relay nodes, which is related to the field of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the proposed algorithm, which is related to the field of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the security of data forwarding, which is related to the field of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
